This is the perfect app for those who like to plan their hikes using a desktop, download the kml/gpx files to their phone, and then use an app for navigation in a setting without a signal or data connectivity. It is well designed for this task, and aims to do nothing else, which I consider the right trade-off with respect to speed/responsiveness and battery consumption.  The interface is simple an intuitive, and compared to some other apps it is very light on the battery (using up about 60% of my phone battery during a 8-hour hike, which is very reasonable; for multi-day hikes I carry a power bank and of course backup maps on paper if available).  The PRO version is well worth it since it allows me to download offline maps, which I found to be high-quality (usually better than paper maps for most countries I visited). Maps are country-specific so it is easy to download the right ones in advance.  I especially like the elevation display one can place below the map, it is very useful when planning rest stops with a group.

content: A very good app that I use a lot! Unfortunately, for some reason, when I updated the Swedish (offline) map a couple of days ago, I got problems. The previous version of the map was over 1 GB in size, the new one is only 622 MB! And now there are several issues with the new map:  - Blank areas appear when panning/zooming, but can be corrected by doing some more panning/zooming around.  - There are less details in the map: ie street names are missing, line segments are now much longer which causes a "jagged" appearance of roads and other structures which should have (and previously had) smoother curvatures.  Roundabouts are square, not round! I believe the issues are in the map itself, and not in the app. Therefore I will give it a 5 star rating anyway. With the hope that the developer checks why this happened and corrects it.  I did the map upgrade on both my phone and the tablet, with exactly the same issues.   ------ EDIT 15 Dec 2018: Yes, now it works! Thanks a lot, fantastic support! With this kind of support it is no wonder that this app is one of the best of it¬¥s kind!
replyContent: Hello, thank you for your review and for reporting this issue. I have checked offline map of Sweden and it was generated incorrectly. Now it is fixed, you can download an update in GPX Viewer PRO.

content: The functionality afforded to power users is simply satisfying. For many years after Google had pulled the plug in its own GPS logging app, I had been using a basic record-and-forget replacement with very few options. For about a month now, I started seeking replacements to all the apps I had been using. I‚Äôve only had this app for about 2 hours, but it has proven to be a worthy replacement for the venerable Google MyTracks. Some improvements I would suggest for this app are additional waypoint types and the ability to cut a route after some time/distance without a GPS signal. I was underground in a train for several stations and when I exited the train from underground, the app drew a straight line from the location I boarded the train to the location I got off. I purchased this app straightaway without touching the free version, but I couldn‚Äôt help but notice how ugly the icon for the pro version is. The overemphasis on ‚ÄúPRO‚Äù is bothersome. If anything, the ‚ÄúPRO‚Äù should be scrubbed from the icon and ‚ÄúFREE‚Äù dropped on the other app‚Äôs icon. It‚Äôs such a blight on what would otherwise be a pretty icon.
replyContent: Hello, thank you for your review and your points. Could I ask you to contact us at gpxviewerpro@vecturagames.com in order to discuss about your points? Thank you.

content: Use it for hiking.  I can find gpx files online.  Awesome tool you have handy.

The free version is great. It was my most useful app. I'm sure that will continue with the PRO version. All functionallity of the free version carried over with no surprises. I was surprised, but very much appreciate, the minimal impact of tracking on battery drain. I look forward to future enhancements. I recommend that anyone using GPX, LOC, or KML/Z files buy this. The offline maps are going to be really useful in an upcoming trip to Europe.
